This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with visual perception and image processing. The use of evolutionary algorithms and machine learning techniques also suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the collaboration of human observers with a computer algorithm, which could place it in the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Finally, the use of top-down expectations and internal representations of scenes suggests that it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
